handNote.seg:
Incipit of each commemorative notice; elements of the punctuation signs (e.g., chains of red and black dots and nine dot asterisks separating the months, chains of red and black dots separating commemorative notices); elements of Ethiopic numerals and coronis-signs.

Several lines or groups of lines on the page opening the commemorative notices for each month are rubricated: 
6 red lines above in groups of 2 alternating with black lines (fols. 20r [Ṭǝqǝmt], 61r [Ṭǝrr], 86r [Yakkātit], 144r [Gǝnbot]); 
4 red lines above alternating with black lines (fols. 104ra [Maggābit], 129rb [Miyāzyā]);
3 red lines above alternating with black lines (fol. 38va [Ḫǝdār], 174va [Naḥāse]).
